…Forum to examine Nigerian ISPs’ viability for digitised environment
…Telecoms operators employ 14,774 Nigerians, 299 expatriates
With data consumption increasing by 70.8 per cent from 205,880.4 terabytes in 2020 to 350,165.39 terabytes in 2021, no less than 552,667 subscribers across the six-geopolitical zones of Nigeria connected to the web via the Internet Service Providers (ISPs) at the end of 2021.  The ISPs had 3,274 employees, where 2,515 were males, 723 females and 36 expatriates. Colocation and Infrastructure sharing providers boasted of 1,920 workers, of which 1,511 were men, 360 women and 49 expatriates. VAS operators had 751 workforce, 526 men and 208 women with 17 expatriates. For other network operators, NCC said they employed 1,426, where 1,160 were men, 258 women and 11 expatriates. 